{"id": 5722, "title": "Ticket #5722: Cache job status queries in the blahp", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe blahp's querying of job status from the batch system is very inefficient and puts a lot of stress on the system. A simple improvement is to have the status script query the status of all jobs and save the results in a cache file. In subsequent invocations, the status script would use the cache file if it's recent enough.\n\n<p>OSG has done this for PBS, and we can take their script. It would be pretty easy to alter this script to produce a version for SLURM.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6136\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6136'); return false;\" title=\"Blahp status python script must accept -w argument\">#6136</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nBlahp status python script must accept -w argument</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-13 17:42</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c61c8a835355533fa6e0965b3d0771599fac14e8\">[48545]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5722'); return false;\" title=\"Cache job status queries in the blahp\">#5722</a></span>) package PBS and SLURM status scripts  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-13 16:20</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/637dce7350de537ad066c03dd1d90da88c25e3c6\">[48544]</a></span>: Docs for cached bulk queries to PBS and SLURM. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5722'); return false;\" title=\"Cache job status queries in the blahp\">#5722</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-13 16:10</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/488595f82fdf6999edd6f92723313c26fe58352b\">[48543]</a></span>: Include slurm_status.py in release. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5722'); return false;\" title=\"Cache job status queries in the blahp\">#5722</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-13 13:30</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/d94c198b8d71a1eac9e0e0308159d74dc18956df\">[48542]</a></span>: Cache job status queries in the blahp for slurm. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5722'); return false;\" title=\"Cache job status queries in the blahp\">#5722</a></span> When querying slurm for job status, capture the status of all jobs and save to a file. In subsequent calls, if cache file is new enough, use its information rather than asking slurm again.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-13 13:29</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/827751025a695b6acf30d593862fafdbbc445150\">[48541]</a></span>: Cache job status queries in the blahp for pbs. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5722\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5722'); return false;\" title=\"Cache job status queries in the blahp\">#5722</a></span> When calling qstat, capture the status of all jobs and save to a file. In subsequent calls, if cache file is new enough, use its information rather than calling qstat again. This code was written by Brian Bockleman and other OSG developers.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2016-Jun-21 15:53", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Jun-10 14:15", "fixed_version": "2016-Jun-10 14:15", "broken_version": "v080400", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Grid", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "osg", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}